the city, and it will be told [to] you what you must do.” 7 And the men who are
journeying with him stood speechless, indeed hearing the voice but seeing no one,
8 and Saul arose from the earth, and his eyes having been opened, he beheld no one,
and leading him by the hand they brought him to Damascus, 9 and he was three days
without seeing, and he neither ate nor drank. 10 And there was a certain disciple in
